President Obama received an update from DHS Secretary Jeh Johnson on the ongoing response and recovery efforts to the severe flooding in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. Secretary Johnson had visited the region on Thursday and met with state and local officials, viewed the ongoing response and recovery efforts, and visited local shelters. The President has been receiving updates on the situation in Louisiana while in Martha's Vineyard, including from the DHS Secretary and the FEMA Administrator. The President has directed his team to coordinate with Louisiana officials to determine an appropriate time for him to visit, and they have determined that he will visit Baton Rouge on Tuesday, August 23rd. The President wants to ensure that his presence does not interfere with ongoing recovery efforts and is eager to get a first-hand look at the impact of the floods and hear from officials about the response. He also wants to assure the people of Louisiana that the American people will be with them as they rebuild their community.